259
00:15:28,920 --> 00:15:31,760
 if you don't have a Bible, you can follow along on the screen.

260
00:15:31,760 --> 00:15:36,200
 So first thing we know about these 3.2 billion,

261
00:15:36,200 --> 00:15:37,680
 they have knowledge of God.

262
00:15:37,680 --> 00:15:41,160
 They have knowledge of God.

263
00:15:41,160 --> 00:15:44,400
 This is Romans chapter one, verse 18.

264
00:15:44,400 --> 00:15:46,240
 The wrath of God is being revealed from heaven

265
00:15:46,240 --> 00:15:48,400
 against all the godlessness and wickedness of men

266
00:15:48,400 --> 00:15:50,160
 who suppress the truth of God by their wickedness

267
00:15:50,160 --> 00:15:54,920
 since what may be known about God is plain to them

268
00:15:54,920 --> 00:15:58,720
 because God has made it plain to them.

269
00:15:59,680 --> 00:16:00,680
 For since the creation of the world,

270
00:16:00,680 --> 00:16:02,240
 God's invisible qualities, his eternal power

271
00:16:02,240 --> 00:16:04,080
 and divine nature have been clearly seen,

272
00:16:04,080 --> 00:16:05,480
 being understood from what has been made

273
00:16:05,480 --> 00:16:10,480
 so that men are without excuse, clearly seen who God is.

274
00:16:10,480 --> 00:16:15,680
 Then it says in verse 21, although they knew God,

275
00:16:15,680 --> 00:16:17,800
 they have knowledge of God.

276
00:16:17,800 --> 00:16:22,480
 All the people in the red, no matter where they live,

277
00:16:22,480 --> 00:16:25,240
 who they are, have knowledge of God.

278
00:16:25,240 --> 00:16:27,800
 God's revealed himself in creation

279
00:16:27,800 --> 00:16:29,320
 to every single one of them.

280
00:16:29,320 --> 00:16:36,120
 Of course, they don't all acknowledge or believe in God,

281
00:16:36,120 --> 00:16:39,160
 which leads to the second thing about them.

282
00:16:39,160 --> 00:16:42,240
 They have all rejected God.

283
00:16:42,240 --> 00:16:46,440
 Romans chapter one, verse 21 makes this clear.

284
00:16:46,440 --> 00:16:49,840
 Although they knew God, they neither glorified him as God

285
00:16:49,840 --> 00:16:52,480
 nor gave thanks to him, but their thinking became futile

286
00:16:52,480 --> 00:16:54,400
 and their foolish hearts were darkened.

287
00:16:54,400 --> 00:16:56,240
 Although they claimed to be wise, they became fools

288
00:16:56,240 --> 00:16:58,880
 and exchanged the glory of the immortal God for images

289
00:16:58,880 --> 00:17:00,160
 made to look like mortal man and birds

290
00:17:00,160 --> 00:17:01,680
 and animals and reptiles.

291
00:17:01,680 --> 00:17:02,640
 Therefore God gave them over

292
00:17:02,640 --> 00:17:03,960
 from the sinful desire of their hearts

293
00:17:03,960 --> 00:17:05,720
 to sexual impurity for the degrading of their bodies

294
00:17:05,720 --> 00:17:06,680
 with one another.

295
00:17:06,680 --> 00:17:09,080
 They exchanged the truth of God for a lie

296
00:17:09,080 --> 00:17:12,080
 and they worshiped and served created things

297
00:17:12,080 --> 00:17:15,360
 rather than the creator who is forever praised.

298
00:17:15,360 --> 00:17:18,280
 So they all rejected God.

299
00:17:18,280 --> 00:17:19,840
 They've not glorified him as God.

300
00:17:19,840 --> 00:17:21,960
 They've turned aside from him as God.

301
00:17:21,960 --> 00:17:24,240
 And to be clear, this is not just talking about

302
00:17:24,240 --> 00:17:29,000
 them, it's talking about every single person in the world,

303
00:17:29,000 --> 00:17:34,000
 yellow, green, red, including every single one of us

304
00:17:34,000 --> 00:17:37,800
 in this gathering tonight.

305
00:17:37,800 --> 00:17:42,240
 This is the reality of sin in every single person's heart,

306
00:17:42,240 --> 00:17:45,720
 in my heart, in your heart, and in every person

307
00:17:45,720 --> 00:17:46,560
 around the world.

308
00:17:46,560 --> 00:17:48,840
 We have all sinned against God.

309
00:17:48,840 --> 00:17:51,560
 We've turned aside from God's ways to our own ways,

310
00:17:51,560 --> 00:17:54,360
 from God's truth to our thoughts.

311
00:17:54,360 --> 00:17:58,920
 We have rejected God and they have all rejected God.

312
00:17:58,920 --> 00:18:03,320
 Which leads to the third truth about them.

313
00:18:03,320 --> 00:18:04,560
 And again, this is not even just talking

314
00:18:04,560 --> 00:18:05,400
 about those in the red.

315
00:18:05,400 --> 00:18:07,240
 In a way, this applies to all of us.

316
00:18:07,240 --> 00:18:10,240
 None of them are innocent before God.

317
00:18:10,240 --> 00:18:13,520
 Not one of them.

318
00:18:13,520 --> 00:18:16,920
 These initial chapters in Romans are so sobering.

319
00:18:16,920 --> 00:18:21,920
 From Romans 1, 18 to 2, 16, you see the sinfulness

320
00:18:21,920 --> 00:18:25,280
 of Gentiles outside of the covenant people of God.

321
00:18:25,280 --> 00:18:26,640
 Then around chapter two, verse 17,

322
00:18:26,640 --> 00:18:28,240
 all the way to chapter three, verse eight,

323
00:18:28,240 --> 00:18:30,360
 you see the Jewish people, covenant people of God,

324
00:18:30,360 --> 00:18:31,760
 described in their sinfulness.

325
00:18:31,760 --> 00:18:34,640
 And then you get to verse nine, or verse 10,

326
00:18:34,640 --> 00:18:37,680
 it says, "As it is written, there is no one righteous,

327
00:18:37,680 --> 00:18:39,840
 "not even one."

328
00:18:39,840 --> 00:18:41,080
 No one.

329
00:18:41,080 --> 00:18:42,920
 So see the repetition here, who understands?

330
00:18:42,920 --> 00:18:44,480
 No one who seeks God.

331
00:18:44,480 --> 00:18:46,000
 All have turned away.

332
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:47,400
 They've become worthless.

333
00:18:47,400 --> 00:18:51,740
 There is no one who does good, not even one.

334
00:18:51,740 --> 00:18:55,280
 Could it be any clearer that all people

335
00:18:55,280 --> 00:18:58,000
 are guilty of sin before God?

336
00:18:58,000 --> 00:19:00,760
 And here's why this is so important,

337
00:19:00,760 --> 00:19:04,680
 because I think about how this question is most often asked.

338
00:19:04,680 --> 00:19:08,600
 Somebody will say to me, "What do you think happens

339
00:19:08,600 --> 00:19:11,240
 "to the innocent man or woman or child

340
00:19:11,240 --> 00:19:14,040
 "in X part of the world who never hears the gospel?"

341
00:19:15,440 --> 00:19:18,360
 If you ask me that question, I would say,

342
00:19:18,360 --> 00:19:21,400
 based on the word of God,

343
00:19:21,400 --> 00:19:24,520
 that person without question goes to heaven,

344
00:19:24,520 --> 00:19:28,020
 even though they've never heard the gospel.

345
00:19:28,020 --> 00:19:33,200
 If they're innocent, why do they need to hear

346
00:19:33,200 --> 00:19:34,760
 how they can be saved from sin?

347
00:19:34,760 --> 00:19:38,120
 Of course they go to heaven.

348
00:19:38,120 --> 00:19:40,520
 The only problem is they don't exist.

349
00:19:40,520 --> 00:19:44,000
 There's no innocent people in the world

350
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:45,600
 just waiting to hear the gospel.

351
00:19:45,600 --> 00:19:47,480
 There's guilty people all over the world.

352
00:19:47,480 --> 00:19:49,480
 That's why they need to hear the gospel.

353
00:19:49,480 --> 00:19:52,000
 See how even when we ask the question,

354
00:19:52,000 --> 00:19:54,640
 we always bias it against God and toward us

355
00:19:54,640 --> 00:19:58,560
 as if God is unjustly putting innocent people

356
00:19:58,560 --> 00:20:00,560
 in a state of condemnation.

357
00:20:00,560 --> 00:20:04,480
 We have no clue the depth of the sinfulness

358
00:20:04,480 --> 00:20:05,600
 of our own hearts.

359
00:20:05,600 --> 00:20:10,320
 The sinfulness in the world around us.

360
00:20:10,320 --> 00:20:13,080
 There is no one who is innocent before God,

361
00:20:13,080 --> 00:20:17,520
 including every single person in the red

362
00:20:17,520 --> 00:20:21,520
 who is guilty before God, which leads to truth number four.

363
00:20:21,520 --> 00:20:26,520
 They all stand condemned for rejecting God.

364
00:20:26,520 --> 00:20:31,680
 This is the end of this argument,

365
00:20:31,680 --> 00:20:33,720
 this part in Romans chapter three, verse 19.

366
00:20:33,720 --> 00:20:35,000
 We know that whatever the law says,

367
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:36,360
 it says to those who are under the law,

368
00:20:36,360 --> 00:20:39,640
 so that every mouth is silenced.

369
00:20:39,640 --> 00:20:43,320
 The whole world is held accountable to God.

370
00:20:43,320 --> 00:20:45,200
 And no one, there it is again,

371
00:20:45,200 --> 00:20:47,160
 will be declared righteous in God's sight

372
00:20:47,160 --> 00:20:48,040
 by the works of the law.

373
00:20:48,040 --> 00:20:50,120
 In other words, by what he does.

374
00:20:50,120 --> 00:20:52,960
 Rather through the law, we become conscious of sin.

375
00:20:52,960 --> 00:20:57,560
 Not only are all people guilty,

376
00:20:57,560 --> 00:20:59,440
 but there's no amount of good we can do

377
00:20:59,440 --> 00:21:01,200
 to overcome our guilt.

378
00:21:01,200 --> 00:21:05,960
 All people are condemned for rejecting God.

379
00:21:05,960 --> 00:21:08,960
 And that's true regardless of whether or not

380
00:21:08,960 --> 00:21:10,840
 someone has heard the gospel.

381
00:21:10,840 --> 00:21:14,840
 And this is really significant because,

382
00:21:14,840 --> 00:21:16,360
 well, let me ask you a question.

383
00:21:16,360 --> 00:21:18,120
 Like, think about this with me.

384
00:21:18,120 --> 00:21:23,120
 Do you think it would be just for God

385
00:21:23,120 --> 00:21:29,520
 to condemn someone to hell for not believing in the gospel

386
00:21:29,520 --> 00:21:34,000
 if they never had a chance to hear the gospel?

387
00:21:37,600 --> 00:21:40,360
 Do you think it would be just for God

388
00:21:40,360 --> 00:21:44,680
 to condemn someone to hell for not believing in the gospel

389
00:21:44,680 --> 00:21:49,240
 when they never even had a chance to hear the gospel?

390
00:21:49,240 --> 00:21:54,000
 I think the answer to that question is no.

391
00:21:54,000 --> 00:21:59,560
 Not accountable for what they've not heard.

392
00:21:59,560 --> 00:22:05,080
 At the same time, that doesn't mean they go to heaven

393
00:22:05,080 --> 00:22:08,240
 because they're condemned for rejecting the God

394
00:22:08,240 --> 00:22:10,520
 that has been clearly shown to them.

395
00:22:10,520 --> 00:22:14,920
 And here's why this is so important,

396
00:22:14,920 --> 00:22:16,320
 'cause people start to think,

397
00:22:16,320 --> 00:22:18,760
 well, maybe, maybe if,

398
00:22:18,760 --> 00:22:20,960
 because they haven't heard the gospel,

399
00:22:20,960 --> 00:22:23,920
 that God will let them into heaven.

400
00:22:23,920 --> 00:22:27,080
 God is loving, gracious.

401
00:22:27,080 --> 00:22:29,400
 We know he wants them in heaven.

402
00:22:29,400 --> 00:22:30,680
 If they haven't heard the gospel,

403
00:22:30,680 --> 00:22:33,920
 maybe he will let them in because they haven't heard.

404
00:22:34,920 --> 00:22:36,560
 But let's think about that for a second.

405
00:22:36,560 --> 00:22:38,800
 If that were true,

406
00:22:38,800 --> 00:22:40,720
 then what is the worst thing we could do

407
00:22:40,720 --> 00:22:42,280
 for all the people in the red?

408
00:22:42,280 --> 00:22:45,920
 Tell them the gospel.

409
00:22:45,920 --> 00:22:50,800
 If they have not heard the gospel,

410
00:22:50,800 --> 00:22:53,000
 and that is some kind of pass into heaven,

411
00:22:53,000 --> 00:22:55,040
 and we get there and we're like,

412
00:22:55,040 --> 00:22:56,560
 I wanna tell you the good news,

413
00:22:56,560 --> 00:22:59,560
 and because we've come with the good news,

414
00:22:59,560 --> 00:23:02,120
 now there's a chance they could go to hell,

415
00:23:02,120 --> 00:23:04,760
 they'd be like, just keep it to yourself.

416
00:23:04,760 --> 00:23:07,040
 And just think about it practically.

417
00:23:07,040 --> 00:23:09,560
 You walk up on the streets of somebody in Dallas,

418
00:23:09,560 --> 00:23:12,040
 you say to someone, have you heard

419
00:23:12,040 --> 00:23:14,080
 the God's love for you and Jesus?

420
00:23:14,080 --> 00:23:16,360
 They say, no, I don't know anything about that.

421
00:23:16,360 --> 00:23:18,280
 If you believe that person is going to heaven

422
00:23:18,280 --> 00:23:20,040
 precisely because they've never heard,

423
00:23:20,040 --> 00:23:21,440
 then what do you say to them?

424
00:23:21,440 --> 00:23:25,200
 Say, well, somebody tries to tell you about Jesus,

425
00:23:25,200 --> 00:23:26,720
 just put your fingers in your ears

426
00:23:26,720 --> 00:23:29,360
 and start yelling really loud and run the other way.

427
00:23:30,280 --> 00:23:33,840
 And this is the whole point of the enterprise of the church,

428
00:23:33,840 --> 00:23:36,800
 this is what we do, this is good news

429
00:23:36,800 --> 00:23:40,520
 that we proclaim to people who have rejected God.

430
00:23:40,520 --> 00:23:43,560
 The point here is that regardless

431
00:23:43,560 --> 00:23:45,880
 of whether or not someone has heard the gospel,

432
00:23:45,880 --> 00:23:48,760
 all people stand guilty before God and sin

433
00:23:48,760 --> 00:23:51,720
 and deserve eternal separation from Him.

434
00:23:51,720 --> 00:23:56,440
 They all stand condemned for rejecting God.

435
00:23:58,320 --> 00:24:00,800
 And at this point, I picture Paul writing the book of Romans

436
00:24:00,800 --> 00:24:03,080
 and it's been two chapters worth

437
00:24:03,080 --> 00:24:04,560
 of just the sinfulness of man,

438
00:24:04,560 --> 00:24:07,000
 all the way to chapter three, verse 20.

439
00:24:07,000 --> 00:24:09,280
 Picture him with tears in his eyes,

440
00:24:09,280 --> 00:24:13,280
 but then I picture him picking up the pen

441
00:24:13,280 --> 00:24:18,280
 and writing, but now, our righteousness from God,

442
00:24:18,280 --> 00:24:20,480
 apart from the law has been made known.

443
00:24:20,480 --> 00:24:22,800
 And this righteousness from God comes through faith

444
00:24:22,800 --> 00:24:25,200
 in Jesus Christ for all who believe.

445
00:24:25,200 --> 00:24:27,440
 There is no difference for all have sinned

446
00:24:27,440 --> 00:24:32,120
 and fall what, short of the glory of God and our.

447
00:24:32,120 --> 00:24:36,680
 Oh, don't just memorize the bad news.

448
00:24:36,680 --> 00:24:38,320
 They are, I think I got it up here,

449
00:24:38,320 --> 00:24:41,480
 justified freely by His grace

450
00:24:41,480 --> 00:24:43,920
 and the redemption that came by Christ Jesus.

451
00:24:43,920 --> 00:24:47,200
 Truth number five, God loves them

452
00:24:47,200 --> 00:24:49,800
 and God has made a way of salvation

453
00:24:49,800 --> 00:24:52,640
 for all 3.2 billion of them.

454
00:24:54,200 --> 00:24:59,200
 God loves them just like God loves us.

455
00:24:59,200 --> 00:25:03,760
 This is the gospel.

456
00:25:03,760 --> 00:25:07,920
 God has made a way for us to be saved from our sin.

457
00:25:07,920 --> 00:25:13,480
 I don't assume everybody who's here tonight

458
00:25:13,480 --> 00:25:15,200
 has put your faith in Jesus.

459
00:25:15,200 --> 00:25:16,120
 Hear this good news.

460
00:25:16,120 --> 00:25:19,240
 Maybe this is the first time you are hearing the gospel.

461
00:25:19,240 --> 00:25:21,240
 It's the greatest news in the world.

462
00:25:21,240 --> 00:25:23,200
 Though you have sinned against God

463
00:25:23,200 --> 00:25:24,720
 and are separated from Him

464
00:25:24,720 --> 00:25:26,840
 and deserve eternal separation from Him,

465
00:25:26,840 --> 00:25:29,280
 God has not left you alone in this state.

466
00:25:29,280 --> 00:25:32,560
 God has come to us in the person of Jesus.

467
00:25:32,560 --> 00:25:34,640
 He has lived the life we could not live,

468
00:25:34,640 --> 00:25:36,760
 a life of no sin.

469
00:25:36,760 --> 00:25:39,680
 And then even though He had no sin for which to die,

470
00:25:39,680 --> 00:25:42,680
 He chose to die on a cross to pay the price

471
00:25:42,680 --> 00:25:44,960
 for the sins of anyone who would trust in Him.

472
00:25:44,960 --> 00:25:46,520
 He lived the life we couldn't live.

473
00:25:46,520 --> 00:25:49,200
 He died the death that we deserve to die.

474
00:25:49,200 --> 00:25:50,800
 And the good news keeps getting better

475
00:25:50,800 --> 00:25:52,840
 'cause He didn't stay dead for long.

476
00:25:52,840 --> 00:25:55,400
 Three days later, He rose from the grave

477
00:25:55,400 --> 00:25:58,000
 in victory over sin and death

478
00:25:58,000 --> 00:25:59,800
 so that anyone, anywhere,

479
00:25:59,800 --> 00:26:01,360
 including anybody in this gathering

480
00:26:01,360 --> 00:26:03,720
 and anybody in the red who turns from their sin

481
00:26:03,720 --> 00:26:05,000
 and trusts in Jesus,

482
00:26:05,000 --> 00:26:07,320
 God will forgive you of all your sin

483
00:26:07,320 --> 00:26:10,800
 and restore you to relationship with Him for eternal life.

484
00:26:10,800 --> 00:26:12,080
 (congregation applauding)

485
00:26:12,080 --> 00:26:14,080
 It's the gospel.

486
00:26:14,080 --> 00:26:18,240
 It's the greatest news in the world.

487
00:26:18,240 --> 00:26:22,400
 (congregation laughing)

488
00:26:22,400 --> 00:26:24,040
 And it's not just for us.

489
00:26:24,040 --> 00:26:27,480
 It's for them too.

490
00:26:27,480 --> 00:26:31,680
 Which leads to truth number six.

491
00:26:31,680 --> 00:26:37,720
 They cannot come to God apart from faith in Jesus.

492
00:26:37,720 --> 00:26:44,320
 This is the way to eternal life.

493
00:26:45,680 --> 00:26:49,840
 Faith in Jesus, verse 27 in Romans 3.

494
00:26:49,840 --> 00:26:50,840
 "Where then is boasting?

495
00:26:50,840 --> 00:26:51,680
 "It's excluded.

496
00:26:51,680 --> 00:26:52,520
 "On what principle?

497
00:26:52,520 --> 00:26:53,340
 "That of observing the law?

498
00:26:53,340 --> 00:26:54,920
 "No, but on that of faith.

499
00:26:54,920 --> 00:26:57,800
 "A man is justified, made right before God

500
00:26:57,800 --> 00:27:01,080
 "by faith apart from observing the law."

